        embed_id: "d7a55902-609b-4da4-bed9-6cdbc3aa3dff",
        type: "social_post",
        content: "id: \"116697945683857980\"\nplatform: mastodon\npage: Mastodon@mastodon.social\ntitle: \"@Mastodon: Following the @EUCommission Tech Sovereignty and Open Source Strategy (and Masto\"\nbody: \"Following the @EUCommission Tech Sovereignty and Open Source Strategy (and Mastodon’s direct mention within it!) announced this week…\\nOur team is proud to have signed and contributed to the drafting of the European Social Stack Open Declaration alongside our peers in the #SocialWeb and #Fediverse: @anewsocial, @eurosky.social, @newsmast, Save Social, and @swf.\\nWe are a movement, and stronger together.\\nRead the declaration, add your signature, and share: https://european.social/\"\nauthor: Mastodon\nauthor_display_name: Mastodon\nauthor_avatar_url: \"https://files.mastodon.social/accounts/avatars/000/013/179/original/b4ceb19c9c54ec7e.png\"\nurl: \"https://mastodon.social/@Mastodon/116697945683857980\"\npublished_at: \"2026-06-05T14:22:17.243Z\"\nreply_count: 10\nrepost_count: 431\nlike_count: 635\nmedia_url: \"https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/116/697/966/879/069/399/original/3333e4260688adbd.jpeg\"\nthumbnail_url: \"https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/116/697/966/879/069/399/small/3333e4260688adbd.jpeg\"\nexternal_url: null\nexternal_title: null\ncomments[5]{id,author,author_display_name,body,url,published_at,like_count,reply_count,repost_count}:\n  \"116697966111184010\",HansLWernitz@troet.cafe,hlw 🇪🇺🐘,\"@Mastodon @EUCommission @anewsocial @eurosky.social @newsmast @swf\\n👍✌👏\",\"https://troet.cafe/@HansLWernitz/116697965998553557\",\"2026-06-05T14:27:27.000Z\",1,0,1\n  \"116698031879568503\",rdp@hachyderm.io,Ryan Pollard 💾,\"@Mastodon @EUCommission @anewsocial @eurosky.social @newsmast @swf I'm a North American, but I applaud this and am excited to see your progress. 👏\",\"https://hachyderm.io/@rdp/116698031834105707\",\"2026-06-05T14:44:11.000Z\",1,0,0\n  \"116698053381671345\",esanchis@mastodon.world,Enrique Sanchis,@Mastodon @EUCommission @anewsocial @eurosky.social @newsmast @swf I find this very exciting and promising. But thinking about it... Would it mean that (when using these European networks) you would not be able to interact with people from eg. North America? Don't know if this is the right forum to ask it... Sorry if it is not.,\"https://mastodon.world/@esanchis/116698053342774977\",\"2026-06-05T14:49:39.000Z\",7,3,0\n  \"116698082888164321\",benroyce,ᴮᵉⁿ ᴿᵒʸᶜᵉVOTE IN THE PRIMARIES,\"@esanchis @Mastodon @EUCommission @anewsocial @eurosky.social@bsky.brid.gy @newsmast @swf\\nit's the right forum to ask because i am an american in western new york state interacting with you\",\"https://mastodon.social/@benroyce/116698082888164321\",\"2026-06-05T14:57:10.871Z\",7,0,0\n  \"116698088368883366\",vladcampos,Vladimir Campos,\"@esanchis @Mastodon @EUCommission @anewsocial @eurosky.social @newsmast @swf The protocols are decentralized. It will work just like you are used to in Mastodon. Some instances are hosted in Europe, others are not, but we can all interact with each other and with the rest of the Fediverse.\",\"https://mastodon.social/@vladcampos/116698088368883366\",\"2026-06-05T14:58:34.460Z\",12,1,0\nfetched_comment_count: 5\nprovider: Mastodon\nembed_ref: mastodon-following-the-MI6\napp_id: social_media\nskill_id: get-posts",
        parent_embed_id: "82873936-1703-45f2-97bf-1330316ce50e",
